A store manager had asked the two men to leave after they asked to use the bathroom but had not made any purchases, police said.
Two black men arrested at Philadelphia Starbucks Two black men waiting at a Starbucks in downtown Philadelphia were arrested on April 12.
In the video, Yaffe arrives to tell police that the two men were waiting for him.
“The police did not just happen upon this event — they did not just walk into Starbucks to get a coffee,” he said.
The manager wanted police assistance to remove the two men but regretted that the incident escalated into an arrest, the official said.
